comments: Robinson (NYK) initiates contact with Jones' (NOP) head during the driving shot attempt.
Barrett (NYK) and Alexander-Walker (NOP) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Gibson (NYK) establishes himself in a screening position in Graham's (NOP) path and absorbs the contact.
Barrett (NYK) places his hands to Alexander-Walker's (NOP) hips and marginal contact occurs as Alexander-Walker moves off-ball.
Alexander-Walker (NOP) is already in GIbson's (NYK) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Alexander-Walker (NOP) firms up on his right foot and is bracing for the contact with Gibson (NYK), which Alexander-Walker absorbs.
Gibson (NYK) turns into Graham (NOP) and initiates body contact after Graham has gathered the ball in his left hand.
Graham (NOP) grasps and then quickly releases Walker's (NYK) jersey as Walker sets the pick.
Alexander-Walker (NOP) goes to, not through, Walker's (NYK) space as Walker sets the pick.
Valanciunas (NOP) jumps toward Barrett (NYK) and marginal body contact occurs as Barrett is passing the ball.
After coming together at the same spot, Valanciunas (NOP) briefly grasps Randle's (NYK) right arm and marginal contact occurs as Randle secures the rebound.
Graham (NOP) briefly has his arms around Gibson's (NYK) upper half and quickly releases.
Gibson (NYK) firms up in his screening position in Graham's (NOP) path and absorbs the contact.
Gibson (NYK) goes to, not through, Alexander-Walker's (NOP) space and briefly has his arms around Alexander-Walker's upper half before quickly releasing.
Valanciunas (NOP) firms up in his screening position in Walker's (NYK) path and absorbs the contact.

Gibson (NYK) extends his arm for the rebound and marginal contact with Hart's (NOP) head as Hart secures the ball. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Barrett (NYK) makes clean forearm contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Hart (NOP) before incidental arm contact occurs.
Marshall (NOP) commits a take foul on Barrett (NYK).
Gibson's (NYK) left hand extends forward and brushes Jones' (NOP) right arm after his gather. Gibson then absorbs the marginal body contact as he jumps alongside Jones' path during the shot attempt.
Hart (NOP) commits a take foul on Barrett (NYK).
Jones (NOP) commits a take foul on Walker (NYK).
Valanciunas (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in Walker's (NYK) path and absorbs the contact.
Randle (NYK) moves toward Valanciunas (NOP) and marginal contact occurs to Valanciunas' side as he receives the pass.
Walker (NYK) applies a stayed forearm to Graham's (NOP) side and Walker removes his arm as Graham elevates for his shot attempt.
Alexander-Walker (NOP) attempts to commit a take foul on Walker (NYK) and the contact is marginal.
